This paper discusses the failure modes of overoptimization in machine learning and artificial intelligence alignment, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also mentions economic regulation and public policy, which could place it in the cs.EC and cs.CY sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of Goodhart effects in the context of increased optimization power offered by artificial intelligence, which could place it in the cs.SI sub-category.
